abstract: The state’s attorney general is publishing guidelines meant to help companies comply with a new privacy law that went into effect Jan. 1.
snippet: The state’s attorney general is publishing guidelines meant to help companies comply with a new privacy law that went into effect Jan. 1.
lead_paragraph: Every major Internet browser has a feature that lets you tell a website that you don’t want it to collect personal information about you when you visit.

abstract: The flood shows the frustration of California gun owners and the complicated politics of weapon regulation in a state with a large catalog of gun control legislation.
snippet: The flood shows the frustration of California gun owners and the complicated politics of weapon regulation in a state with a large catalog of gun control legislation.
lead_paragraph: SANTA ANA, Calif. — Pete Alexander celebrated the news that a federal court in California had thrown out this state’s strict requirements for obtaining a concealed-handgun permit — among the toughest in the nation — by calling the Orange County Sheriff’s Department to apply for a permit he had long wanted.

abstract: Critics say a judge erred when he accepted Facebook’s argument that a federal privacy law for children under 13 preempted state protections for older children.
snippet: Critics say a judge erred when he accepted Facebook’s argument that a federal privacy law for children under 13 preempted state protections for older children.
lead_paragraph: A couple of government wingmen have joined privacy groups in their legal dogfight with Facebook over the company’s use of teenagers’ likes and comments in advertising.

abstract: Three nonprofit groups want Gov. Jerry Brown to return $369 million used to pay down state debt, rather than help struggling homeowners.
snippet: Three nonprofit groups want Gov. Jerry Brown to return $369 million used to pay down state debt, rather than help struggling homeowners.
lead_paragraph: Three nonprofit groups offering homeowner counseling sued Gov. Jerry Brown of California on Friday, demanding the state replace $369 million that had been earmarked to help troubled borrowers but was used instead to pay down the state’s debt.

abstract: India, the second-largest exporter of over-the-counter and prescription drugs to the United States, is coming under increased scrutiny by American regulators.
snippet: India, the second-largest exporter of over-the-counter and prescription drugs to the United States, is coming under increased scrutiny by American regulators.
lead_paragraph: NEW DELHI — India, the second-largest exporter of over-the-counter and prescription drugs to the United States, is coming under increased scrutiny by American regulators for safety lapses, falsified drug test results and selling fake medicines.

abstract: Smith & Wesson objects to a technology called microstamping, which prints a unique code on shell casings to make it easier to trace weapons used in crimes.
snippet: Smith & Wesson objects to a technology called microstamping, which prints a unique code on shell casings to make it easier to trace weapons used in crimes.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Smith & Wesson, the firearms manufacturer, announced Thursday that it would not sell new semiautomatic pistols in California because of its objections to a gun safety law that took effect in the state last May.
headline_main: Gun Maker Will Limit Sales in Protest of California Law
headline_print_headline: Gun Maker Will Limit Sales in Protest of California Law

abstract: The case against JPMorgan may set a precedent for cases against other major banks and industries like health care, where fines have been growing.

abstract: The California attorney general’s office has shut down 10 websites that mimicked state’s official health insurance marketplace.
snippet: The California attorney general’s office has shut down 10 websites that mimicked state’s official health insurance marketplace.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES—The California attorney general’s office has shut down 10 websites that mimicked state’s official health insurance marketplace, the attorney general, Kamala Harris, announced Wednesday.
headline_main: California Shuts Down Sites Mimicking State Insurance Marketplace

abstract: Two of the central players in the biggest settlement of the financial crisis were once on opposite sides of the negotiating table.
snippet: Two of the central players in the biggest settlement of the financial crisis were once on opposite sides of the negotiating table.
lead_paragraph: At the end of a conference call on the night of Oct. 18, JPMorgan Chase’s chief executive and the attorney general left their top lieutenants to hash out the details of a tentative $13 billion settlement. The talks, led Tony West, the associate attorney general at the Justice Department, and Stephen M. Cutler, JPMorgan’s general counsel, could still fall apart over how much wrongdoing the bank will admit on its questionable mortgage practices.
headline_main: Weekend Reading: 2 Key Players in JPMorgan’s $13 Billion Deal

abstract: The nonprofit, which has ties to the billionaire conservative businessmen Charles and David Koch, failed to disclose over $15 million in contributions it funneled into California referendum battles.
snippet: The nonprofit, which has ties to the billionaire conservative businessmen Charles and David Koch, failed to disclose over $15 million in contributions it funneled into California referendum battles.
lead_paragraph: A secretive nonprofit group with ties to the billionaire conservative businessmen Charles and David Koch admitted to improperly failing to disclose more than $15 million in contributions it funneled into state referendum battles in California, state officials there announced Thursday.
